                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client who has a chest tube drainage system following a right lobectomy to treat lung cancer. While the client is being assisted to sit up in bed in preparation for ambulation, the chest tube accidentally disconnects from the chest tube drainage system. Which is the initial nursing action?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIf a chest tube becomes disconnected, the nurse would as quickly as possible place the end of the tube in a container of sterile water until the drainage system can be replaced. It is not necessary to contact a respiratory therapist at this time. It may be necessary to contact the PHCP, but this would not be the initial nursing action. Asking the client to perform a Valsalva maneuver is not appropriate and could be harmful.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Complex Care: Emergency Situations/Management\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Cancer: Laryngeal and Lung\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Gas Exchange, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Strategic Words Test-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, initial. Focus on the physiology of the chest tube drainage system to answer this question. Recalling that maintenance of the underwater seal drainage is essential will assist in directing you to the correct option.",
                        "id": "6217c171d9ce48d4b82084a76f0cf81d",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "124e4cd6dd6e40c792dec9db57456888",
                                "content": "Monitor the client's airway."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "fc9f136ecdb44533983bbe48ed4312ac",
                                "content": "Call the Rapid Response Team."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "81b16bbaed224034bf7fdaa249dc880d",
                                "content": "Apply manual pressure over the site."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f61f88c0ada64dae97bc94df27ee286f",
                                "content": "Lower the head of the bed to a flat position."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
