                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The client who has had a radical neck dissection to treat laryngeal cancer begins to hemorrhage at the incision site. Which immediate actions would the nurse take? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIf the client begins to hemorrhage from the surgical site following radical neck dissection, the nurse elevates the head of the bed to maintain airway patency and prevent aspiration. The nurse applies pressure over the bleeding site, stays with the client, and asks someone to call the Rapid Response Team and the PHCP immediately.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Complex Care: Emergency Situations/Management\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Cancer: Laryngeal and Lung\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Perfusion, Safety\nStrategies: ABCs—Airway, Breathing, Circulation, Strategic Words                    Test-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, immediate. Use the ABCs—airway, breathing, and circulation. Monitoring the client's airway and applying pressure over the site are indicated if the client is hemorrhaging. Calling the Rapid Response Team and the PHCP is also indicated immediately, but lowering the head of the bed does not help with airway maintenance.",
                        "id": "a6043871f6b4415785317296924c2cd0",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
